# Verify paths before citing them

When writing review artifacts, walkthroughs, or answering “where is this?” questions:

- Verify that a referenced file path actually exists in the current workspace/worktree before asserting it.
- Prefer citing grep/search results (or a direct file read) over memory of earlier branch states.
- If a path has moved, update all review artifacts that reference the old location in the same session.

